## What blocked

Host Docker daemon (29.4.1 / containerd 2.2.3) returns:
    failed to create task for container: failed to start shim:
    start failed: failed to create TTRPC connection:
    unsupported protocol: Yunix

on *every* container start, including `docker run --rm hello-world`.
Confirmed against a clean image pull at 2026-05-28T08:47:27+00:00.

This is a host-level containerd/docker integration fault unrelated to
the compose file. The daemon has been up 2 weeks 3 days with ~750
running containers and 9094 containerd tasks; resource/state exhaustion
is the likely cause. Recovery requires `systemctl restart containerd
docker.service` which the agent must not perform unilaterally — there
are 750 running user workloads on this host.

